    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-07-09T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-07-09T05:00:00-05:00" n="534"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d534">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/383: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Third Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Allison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-09T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 9, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 9—4:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. Shanghai’s 893, June 24, 10 a.m. L. J. Mead of Standard Vacuum Oil Company,
                    and T. F. Shields of Texas Company, both American citizens, arrived in Nanking
                    together this afternoon on the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Oahu</hi>. These are
                    the first American businessmen who have returned to Nanking since its occupation
                    by the Japanese.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Hankow, Peiping and Shanghai. Peiping please repeat to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Allison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
